Text1: I strongly believe that my experience with community engagement will enable me to better understand the disparities that affect particular communities, particularly in the context of healthcare. As a prospective healthcare provider, having a strong understanding of these barriers is crucial to directing treatment plans that are tailored to resource accessibility and quality. Therefore, by engaging with community partners and identifying barriers to patient care, I can better inform my clinical decisions to reflect limitations my patients face.
Text2: This quarter, my group is working with a community partner called Watts Rising, an urban development organization that is revitalizing the Watts neighborhood with numerous interventions that remedy community issues, from lack of access to a variety of fresh produce and current stigmas that arise from historical violence to unsafe intersections that result in countless cyclist deaths every year. My project is focused on revitalizing a historically plagued landmark that has often been known as a site for violence and community divisions. Our revitalization efforts aim to highlight positive images of the Watts community whether that is notable figures from Watts or positive landmarks (ie the Watts towers). Our hope is to target community members of all ages to spark conversation of these events and create a community focus on these positive historical highlights.
